<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="415" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1268,1764]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1341,1367]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Remarks.</emphasis>
Following the suggestions of some authors (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Strack, H. L." box="[894,1034,1341,1367]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="12 - 15" refId="ref36473" refString="Strack, H. L. (2003) Class Polyplacophora. In: Hylleberg, J. &amp; Kilburn, R. N. (Eds.), Tropical Marine Mollusc Programme. Marine Molluscs of Vietnam. Phuket Marine Biological Center Special Publication, 28, pp. 12 - 15." type="journal article" year="2003">Strack 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwabe, E." box="[1048,1218,1341,1367]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="3143 - 3173" refId="ref35172" refString="Schwabe, E. (2004) The Polyplacophora (Mollusca) collected during the First International Marine Biodiversity Workshop for Rodrigues (western Indian Ocean), with the description of a new species. Journal of Natural History, 38, 3143 - 3173. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930410001695114" type="journal article" year="2004">Schwabe 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 2006; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwabe, E. &amp; Sirenko, B. I. &amp; Seeto, J." pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="1 - 52" refId="ref35424" refString="Schwabe, E., Sirenko, B. I. &amp; Seeto, J. (2008) A checklist of Polyplacophora (Mollusca) from the Fiji Islands. Zootaxa, 1777 (1), 1 - 52. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1777.1.1" type="journal article" year="2008">
Schwabe 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwabe, E. &amp; Pittman, C." box="[260,555,1377,1403]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="49 - 64" refId="ref35379" refString="Schwabe, E. &amp; Pittman, C. (2014) New records of chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) from Hawaii, including the description of a new species of Weedingia Kaas, 1988. Venus, 72, 49 - 64." type="journal article" year="2014">Schwabe &amp; Pittman 2014</bibRefCitation>
), the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1882" box="[692,785,1377,1403]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Lucilina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[692,785,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Lucilina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here used at full genus level, and not as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gray, 1847" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1847" box="[151,367,1413,1439]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Tonicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,234,1414,1439]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Tonicia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gray, J. E." box="[240,367,1413,1439]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="129 - 206" refId="ref32170" refString="Gray, J. E. (1847) A list of the genera of Recent Mollusca, their synonyms and types. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 15, 129 - 206. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1847. tb 00164. x" type="journal article" year="1847">Gray, 1847</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1847" box="[543,626,1414,1439]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Tonicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[543,626,1414,1439]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Tonicia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are geographically restricted to the South Eastern Pacific region of Latin America with a single species in the Caribbean, while members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1882" box="[903,996,1449,1475]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Lucilina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[903,996,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Lucilina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are widespread throughout the tropical Indo-Pacific.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1268,1764]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1882" box="[199,292,1521,1547]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Lucilina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,292,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Lucilina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is well represented in the Indian Ocean by six species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Reeve, 1847)" baseAuthorityName="Reeve" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[902,1208,1521,1547]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Lucilina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sueziensis">
<emphasis box="[902,1042,1522,1547]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">L. sueziensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Reeve, L." box="[1056,1201,1521,1547]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="21 - 84" refId="ref34646" refString="Reeve, L. (1847) Conchologia iconica, or illustrations of the shells of molluscous animals. Monograph of the genus Chiton. Vol. 4. Reeve, Brothers, London, 64 pp., 28 pls. [pp. 21 - 84]" type="book chapter" year="1847">Reeve, 1847</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Thiele, 1909" authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1909" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Lucilina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perligera">
<emphasis box="[1219,1352,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">L. perligera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thiele, J." pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref37156" refString="Thiele, J. (1909) Revision des Systems der Chitonen. Zoologica, 22, 1 - 132, pls. 1 - 10. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11245" type="journal article" year="1909">Thiele, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sykes, 1903)" baseAuthorityName="Sykes" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[223,550,1557,1583]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Lucilina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pectinoides">
<emphasis box="[223,382,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">L. pectinoides</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sykes, E. R." box="[398,541,1557,1583]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="177 - 180" refId="ref36685" refString="Sykes, E. R. (1903) Report on the Polyplacophora collected by Professor Herdman, at Ceylon, in 1902. Ceylon Pearl Oyster Fisheries, Supplementary Reports, 4, 177 - 180, pl. 1." type="journal article" year="1903">Sykes, 1903</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Leloup, 1936)" baseAuthorityName="Leloup" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[563,883,1557,1584]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Lucilina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ceylonica">
<emphasis box="[563,702,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">L. ceylonica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Leloup, E." box="[718,875,1557,1584]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="51 - 61" refId="ref33470" refString="Leloup, E. (1936) Descriptions de deux especes d'amphineures provenant de Trincomali (Ceylon). Proceedings of the Malacological Society of London, 22 (2), 51 - 61." type="journal article" year="1936">Leloup, 1936</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kaas, 1979)" baseAuthorityName="Kaas" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[896,1173,1557,1583]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Lucilina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="carnosa">
<emphasis box="[896,1017,1558,1583]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">L. carnosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P." box="[1034,1164,1557,1583]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="855 - 879" refId="ref32613" refString="Kaas, P. (1979) The Chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) of Mozambique. Annals of the Natal Museum, 23, 855 - 879." type="journal article" year="1979">Kaas, 1979</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Leloup, 1981)" baseAuthorityName="Leloup" baseAuthorityYear="1981" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Lucilina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis box="[1231,1332,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">L. indica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Leloup, E." pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="1 - 46" refId="ref33662" refString="Leloup, E. (1981) Chitons de Tulear, Reunion, Maurice et Tahiti. Bulletin Institut Royale des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, 53, 1 - 46, 4 pls." type="book chapter" year="1981">Leloup, 1981</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, of which only the first two are known from the 
<collectingRegion box="[762,859,1593,1619]" country="Sudan" name="Al Bahr al Ahmar" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Red Sea</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="415" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1268,1764]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1628,1655]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Distribution.</emphasis>
Widespread in the Indian Ocean, the Indo-Pacific, 
<collectingCountry box="[937,1043,1629,1655]" name="Australia" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Australia</collectingCountry>
, the Central Pacific Ocean and 
<collectingCountry name="Japan" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Japan</collectingCountry>
. The fossil record extends back to the middle Oligocene of 
<collectingCountry box="[857,936,1665,1691]" name="France" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[946,1056,1665,1691]" country="France" name="Aquitaine" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Aquitaine</collectingRegion>
Basin (
<bibRefCitation author="Dell'Angelo, B. &amp; Lesport, J. - F. &amp; Cluzaud, A. &amp; Sosso, M." box="[1141,1424,1665,1691]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref31228" refString="Dell'Angelo, B., Lesport, J. - F., Cluzaud, A. &amp; Sosso, M. (2018 a) The Oligocene to Miocene chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) of the Aquitaine Basin, southwestern France, and Ligerian Basin, western France. Part 1: Leptochitonidae, Hanleyidae, Ischnochitonidae, Chitonidae, Spinochitonidae fam. nov. and Schizochitonidae. Bollettino Malacologico, 54, 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="2018">
Dell’Angelo 
<emphasis box="[1289,1345,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">et al.</emphasis>
2018a
</bibRefCitation>
), the Neogene of west Pacific islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Ladd, H. S." box="[576,703,1701,1727]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="1 - 98" refId="ref33233" refString="Ladd, H. S. (1966) Chitons and Gastropods (Haliotidae through Adeorbidae) from the western Pacific islands. Geological Survey Professional Paper, 531, 1 - 98, 16 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.3133 / pp 531" type="book chapter" year="1966">Ladd 1966</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwabe, E. &amp; Sirenko, B. I. &amp; Seeto, J." box="[717,952,1701,1727]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="1 - 52" refId="ref35424" refString="Schwabe, E., Sirenko, B. I. &amp; Seeto, J. (2008) A checklist of Polyplacophora (Mollusca) from the Fiji Islands. Zootaxa, 1777 (1), 1 - 52. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1777.1.1" type="journal article" year="2008">
Schwabe 
<emphasis box="[827,885,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
) and the Pleistocene of the Red Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Issel, A." pageId="14" pageNumber="415" pagination="243 - 303" refId="ref32417" refString="Issel, A. (1869) Malacologia del Mar Rosso. Ricerche zoologiche e paleontologiche. Parte terza. Catalogo delle conchiglie fossili raccolte sulle spiagge emerse del Mar Rosso. Biblioteca Malacologica, Pisa, 61 pp. [pp. 243 - 303]" type="book chapter" year="1869">Issel 1869</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
